modules.description: Provides functions for parsing IRC messages, managing plugin hooks, and handling connection loops with an IRC server. Operates on data types such as IRC messages, plugin configurations, and event handlers. Used to build bots that respond to channel events, execute commands, and simulate robotic dialogue through predefined scripts.

Provides functions to interact with Redis for message passing, including publishing and subscribing to channels using specified prefixes. Operates on strings for channel names and messages, and integers for port configuration. Used to enable real-time communication between IRC clients through Redis pub/sub mechanisms.
